

what .js-lang can do on HTML page in browser ?

 .js-lang using browser provided APIs, 
  can bring any dynamic functionality to web-page.
  
  
  browser APIs ==> DOM , XHR , Timer , Etc.., all are based on w3c standards
  
  all the browser APIs are implemented by browsers based w3c standards , abstracted as /js objects and functions

using DOM
-----------

  --> can create/retreive/update/delete HTML elements
  --> can change element's attributes 
  --> can change element's style
  --> can change element's text
  --> can listen events on elements
  --> can create rich-UI components
  
  
using XHR
----------  
  --> can communicate with server-side async,update page with resp ( AJAX )
  
using Timer API
----------------

setTimeout() , setInterval()


HTML5 APIs
------------

  a. canvas
  b. audio/video 
  c. webworker
  d. websocket
  e. SSE
  f. storage API
  g. Geo
  etc..
  
  
        
        
        limitations of plain-js
        
        
        
        --> browser compatibility
        --> too much code for simple operns
        --> performance issues ( e.g DOM manipulation )
        --> memory issues
        --> data-binding  manual
        --> code organization
        --> good design paterns
        
